  "slug": "apple-turnovers-puff",
  "title": "Apple turnovers",
  "subtitle": "Puff pastry parcels with spiced apple filling",
  "excerpt": "Ready-made puff pastry folded around a spiced apple filling, brushed with egg wash, and baked until golden and flaky. Quick to make at home with a shop-bought pastry sheet.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Apple turnovers using ready-made puff pastry are documented in British domestic cookery from the mid-twentieth century, when commercially produced puff pastry became widely available. The filling follows the traditional British formula of cooking apple, caster sugar, and warm spice.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A turnover is simply a folded pastry parcel, one square of puff pastry, a spoonful of filling, folded in half and crimped shut. The only technique that matters is sealing the edges properly: press firmly with a fork all the way around, or the filling leaks and the pastry steams rather than crisps.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Pastry"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "puff-pastry",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "1 sheet ready-made, chilled",
                  "quantity": 375,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "free-range-eggs",
                  "unit": null,
                  "prepNote": "beaten, for egg wash",
                  "quantity": 1,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "icing-sugar",
                  "unit": "tbsp",
                  "prepNote": "to dust",
                  "quantity": 1,
                  "isOptional": true
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Apple filling"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "bramley-apples",
                  "unit": null,
                  "prepNote": "medium (about 400 g), peeled, cored, roughly diced",
                  "quantity": 2,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "caster-sugar",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 50,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "ground-cinnamon",
                  "unit": "tsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 0.5,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "lemon-juice",
                  "unit": "tsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 1,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the apple filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the diced {{bramley-apples}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{ground-cinnamon}}, and {{lemon-juice}} in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring, until the apple is just tender and the liquid has reduced to a thick syrup. Spread on a plate to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Line a baking tray with baking paper. Unroll the {{puff-pastry}} sheet and cut into 6 equal squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and seal",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place a spoonful of cooled filling in the centre of each square. Brush the edges with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "egg wash",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp73tbq90000wov4k6oi7wjo"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Fold the pastry over the filling to form a triangle. Press the edges together firmly with a fork. Place on the lined tray.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake, 18 to 22 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the tops with the remaining egg wash. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes until the pastry is deep golden and crisp. Leave on the tray for 5 minutes before moving. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
